    <title>To amend the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act by clarifying that State Exchanges are prohibited from imposing fees or assessments on issuers of excepted benefits and standalone dental plans not sold through an Exchange.</title>
    <updateDate>2019-04-18T16:17:20Z</updateDate>
    <billType>HR</billType>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-03-01T20:32:14Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <updateDate>2017-11-02T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>This bill amends the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act to prohibit a state from funding its health insurance exchange by charging a health insurer a fee or tax&nbsp;for&nbsp;excepted benefits coverage (benefits not subject to requirements under the Act)&nbsp;or standalone dental plans that are not sold on an exchange.</p>]]></text>
          <actionDate>2017-11-02</actionDate>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
